verbose_text: This is in line with our previous studies [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR], and might be due to tissue specific fatty acid processing, given that the liver is the most important organ for fatty acid turnover and metabolism, while in the lung the rather sustained levels of arachidonic acid could be due to arachidonic acid derived prostaglandins and leukotrienes being particularly involved in immune function in the lung.
